-- Popolare di Milano CEO Ponzellini Rules Out Share Sale, Corriere Reports
-- B y   M a r c o   B e r t a c c h e
-- 2010-10-26T06:43:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-26/popolare-di-milano-ceo-ponzellini-rules-out-share-sale-corriere-reports.html
Banca Popolare di Milano Scrl isn’t
considering a capital increase, Chief Executive Officer  Massimo Ponzellini  said in an interview with Corriere della Sera.  Pop. Milano shares “are factoring in the idea of a capital
increase, which won’t happen because there’s no reason for it,”
Ponzellini said. The Milan-based bank plans to rein in spending,
he said.  The shares have fallen 32 percent this year.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Angela Cullen at   acullen8@bloomberg.net  